FRONTLINE ROADS v0.32.7 final source audit

Expected legacy-only identifiers:
- fieldAid: retained only in normalizeCombatState() to migrate old saves.
- recoveryTargetHp / recoveryFacilityType / recoveryFacilityId: retained only as delete operations during squad normalization.
- recoveryCap / recoveryCapacity: retained only as delete operations during old field-aid migration.

Removed runtime responsibilities:
- No field-aid recovery facility definition.
- No recovery facility control of base reorganization duration or queue capacity.
- No ordinary friendly-squad construction anchors.
- No duplicate area-healing queue.

Current responsibilities:
- Expedition squad: moving 120 m construction anchor.
- Recovery facility: spatial continuous healing for all living friendly squads in range.
- Major base: innate return logistics for civilization-level-zero viability.
- Simple base: reorganization only unless a recovery facility covers the squad.
- Field barracks: +1 deployable squad slot at its owning simple base.
